{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN4/manasa-sutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>So I have heard. At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.</p>\n<p>Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“There’s a mental snare <br>\nwandering the sky. <br>\nI’ll bind you with it— <br>\nyou won’t escape me, ascetic!” <br>\n<br>\n“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, <br>\nand touches so delightful: <br>\ndesire for these is gone from me. <br>\nYou’re beaten, terminator!”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN4/patta-sutta/\">SN.4.16. Patta Sutta (“The Alms Bowls”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So I have heard. At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“There’s a mental snare "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwandering the sky. "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nI’ll bind you with it— "},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nyou won’t escape me, ascetic!” "},{"type":"elemen